Let $z = \cos \theta + i \sin \theta.$  Then
\begin{align*}
|1 + z| &= |1 + \cos \theta + i \sin \theta| \\
&= \sqrt{(1 + \cos \theta)^2 + \sin^2 \theta} \\
&= \sqrt{2 + 2 \cos \theta} \\
&= 2 \left| \cos \frac{\theta}{2} \right|,
\end{align*}and
\begin{align*}
|1 - z + z^2| &= |1 - \cos \theta - i \sin \theta + \cos 2 \theta + i \sin 2 \theta| \\
&= |(1 + \cos 2 \theta - \cos \theta) + i (\sin 2 \theta - \sin \theta)| \\
&= \sqrt{(1 + \cos 2 \theta - \cos \theta)^2 + (\sin 2 \theta - \sin \theta)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{2 + 2 \cos 2 \theta - 2 \cos \theta \cos 2 \theta - 2 \sin \theta \sin 2 \theta} \\
&= \sqrt{2 + 2 \cos 2 \theta - 2 \cos 3 \theta} \\
&= 2 \left| \cos \frac{3 \theta}{2} \right|.
\end{align*}Hence,
\[|1 + z| + |1 - z + z^2| = 2 \left| \cos \frac{\theta}{2} \right| + 2 \left| \cos \frac{3 \theta}{2} \right|.\]By the Triangle Inequality,
\[2 \left| \cos \frac{\theta}{2} \right| + 2 \left| \cos \frac{3 \theta}{2} \right| \ge 2 \left| \cos \frac{\theta}{2} + \cos \frac{3 \theta}{2} \right| = 4 \left| \cos \theta \right| \cos \frac{\theta}{2}.\]Equality occurs when $\cos \frac{\theta}{2}$ and $\cos \frac{3 \theta}{2}$ have the same sign, which means $0 \le \theta \le \frac{2 \pi}{3}$ or $\frac{4 \pi}{3} \le \theta \le 2 \pi.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair moo (real t) {
  return((2*cos(t/2),2*cos(3*t/2)));
}

path foo = moo(0);
real t;

for (t = 0; t <= 2*pi + 0.1; t = t + 0.1) {
  foo = foo--moo(t);
}

draw(foo,red);
draw((-2.5,0)--(2.5,0));
draw((0,-2.5)--(0,2.5));
[/asy]

Since $4 \left| \cos \theta \right| \cos \frac{\theta}{2}$ is maximized when $\cos \theta = 1,$ the maximum value is $4 \cos \frac{\pi}{2} = \boxed{0}.$

